  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "libidn security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libidn is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "GNU Libidn is a fully documented implementation of the Stringprep, Punycode and IDNA 2003 specifications. Libidn\u0026apos;s purpose is to encode and decode internationalized domain names.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nGNU libidn before 1.44 is prone to out-of-bounds reads of uninitialized memory in the ToUnicode APIs because of mishandling in idna_to_unicode_internal. The affected code is not present in libidn2.(CVE-2026-57053)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libidn is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "libidn",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
